[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test setup**\n\nI see that marks should be provided by default when using the library, according to the documentation. The Maven plugin environment gives access to it. If I'm testing `createContextForSkin` with a skin artifact, I'll need the extra `maven-artifact`, which existing tests may have overlooked. To achieve meaningful site rendering, I might bypass the skin artifact by manually setting the template classloader or name. I’ll need to check the default template in the `SiteRenderingContext` as well. The old tests relied on `context.setUsingDefaultTemplate(true)`, but that's been removed, so I'll need to find a new approach.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_010fac517b7651d6016a400d14e6bc8196a8ba97f48943adb3\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQA0e7CgXWs_eEuJazxzrLWRd8deSg66lDi_E-Lxn_DFvSFFgIgOsyvVh0STpgF5Ed-KJrwjotfJ2qmc3WT_NtnMMJ3Q_0eI7JVGxfpG5Ah6nUynu0MfbLIphhrykwy6BfOhHC3OSPFOa0Gp-jXpxvblS1yJAA8aDrcwFEn0Et8Fw4beoTAI6cd72Z-ZnjMA3kBOFUHMwayZ7XsI6EhSzwlKpHktqdR8-GN91mCyh70DvEDRNW_UPMfXOMAHAcirKtQKEblVJps5waDjtqU4It-sr1CPXM6br9fr-eQCETb30EMPEOiu72nVXny2xKzIemhML2-eJx-f9np7blvRu4S8wB2D2UkO43Q1SdYVBE5qVf4QAtbkkyoq4t1iZ6TP60Wa-DSuH4ZFuL1eEMOFIQ4UzvdTUOzHGm_Am3XHTiNZtBTra7CUbLtApG3M7f_vSzqn2lDUx5Qrxcv0vd1Q2ODFf47-ya0ZMWkDUndvfUh293rM2Dt2zKs0LrMcoJxmzh84Cp7HB8vvNUBARsCUsFVV3PbLexS3Lb2KKLn643Xo4Pi7uNyx1GT95dDtGac-yKLPEbVxzZkamjrhEkkcw41cisFDRG_rbZLVo0Nk4Ji1xLZRHhthDV1gCoxZKsANCJVmcwNpaG75sVqBS7sJZHNqZo49QdhsIkg_z3Kzl_dnzbzfQe9gNZ-TKYn_T2vkafrQJLOzhJDf4UaBCLoxI--GaRjvuPxX3IX0mmXgQDhiMG5rZhbqm3Q5x4LJ4Zaf9JmeYEMaQeRz42TrWdcSstOnIZK0fH2hyGwCGeWQy7zP2Z9QW5ZHtjGht9cLxi4jpo48iY7Kc_r6whFnDTxCokVRwMgM1JJ_1sDGy2deqRO0xtEYRq4cVjRPKVhUOEWwKHZuKPPM0TYspVJi9vLaBlb8eC7RNb4M-3jm6Y6aCoNw-Szj3j0bxyhgoptwGpLee2Nx92pPuQlW8qUZy9CcPZrPEPgP8B4t_mac4N-fCwGdx2YLLwXwenVJFrIH2-RjoMXAumbz1VnDqcBtVFVSJtSS9v1MV6vKxWzJ1Nokpr60wWplaBEUeRuf1C