 \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-apt:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Upstream doxia-site-renderer tests add this parser module explicitly because Doxia modules are no longer all in doxia-core and their component descriptors must be on the test classpath for site document discovery/rendering.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-xdoc:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"XDoc rendering is a normal Doxia Site Renderer use case, but the parser module is test-scoped upstream and is not pulled transitively by doxia-site-renderer.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-module-fml:2.0.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"FML rendering is covered by upstream site-renderer tests, but the parser module is not a runtime transitive dependency of doxia-site-renderer.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Do not directly instantiate DefaultSiteRenderer for rendering tests unless its injected fields are populated; in 2.0.0 it uses javax.inject fields for VelocityComponent, ParserModuleManager, Doxia, and PlexusContainer. Prefer looking up SiteRenderer/DefaultSiteRenderer from a Plexus/Sisu container available on the transitive classpath, or otherwise inject those collaborators deliberately in test code. No Docker image or environment/system property setup appears necessary.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The existing 1.9.1 tests use removed/changed APIs such as RenderingContext, SkinResourceLoader, enableLogging, and setUsingDefaultTemplate; setup alone will not fix the javac failure.\",\n    \"The public skin-related API references org.apache.maven.artifact.Artifact, which is a provided dependency upstream; tests that specifically exercise createContextForSkin or skin artifacts may need to avoid compile-time coupling or add a matching Maven artifact dependency during test implementation.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_010fac517b7651d6016a400d31256481969bcfbc0e7eb83874\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 342, "output": 1061, "cacheRead": 43008, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44411, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782582567853, "responseId": "resp_010fac517b7651d6016a400d2875d08196a04f982c12959562"}, "toolResults": []}
